{
  "stem": "13313.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that's when the school closed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There still was, but the-- but the--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were still Jewish teachers teaching it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the emphasis, the authority, was more or less in the hands of pro-- of pro-German staff, which obviously were not-- there were no longer a Hebrew principal.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, as a matter of fact, our friendly Gentile principal had been replaced as well, all staffed by pro-- and the teachers, the-- the ones that do the Brownshirts, they-- they-- they delighted in beating up the kids once in a while in class for no reason and insulting us for being Jewish and all that because they were actually Nazis.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Totally non-Jewish neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were not observant, although I was aware that my father was very Jewish in a nationalistic way, in an ethnic identifying way, very proud.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he was not raised in the tradition himself because he didn't have a father when he was young.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Had to go to work.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So it was totally non-observant.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But, as I said, ethnically, very much identifying with the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Very proud, as well, of our heritage.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So as a result, we-- the language we spoke at home was actually the local Flemish, which was the Dutch dialect, and-- whereas most of the Jewish community would not speak that language because it was considered the language of the peasantry or the poor people.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was looked down at, and the better-to-do people would all speak French.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "French was the language of the aristocracy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Flemish was the language of the other-- of the proletariat, if you want, and of the local people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And French was a world language, and Flemish was only a local language.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So-- also, most of the more religious Jews would naturally speak Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
